  "difficulty": "L2",
  "snapshot": "os",
  "instruction": "A local implementation brief is already available in Chrome at file:///home/user/Desktop/accessible_signup_brief.html. Use VS Code to refine /home/user/Desktop/accessible_signup from the provided starter into an accessible, previewable signup flow. Keep the form wrapper and the local illustration assets/form-scene.svg. Add span.error-text regions with aria-live=polite for the name, email, and password fields. Add a checkbox input#terms with a visible agreement label. Add section#success-panel below the form with a heading that includes Ready to launch. In app.js, validate the form using browser validity APIs with custom messages, including setCustomValidity and reportValidity. Update manifest.json so project is accessible-signup-refine, theme is harbor, validationMode is inline-live, and previewPort is 8124. Start a local preview server for the project and finish with Chrome open at http://127.0.0.1:8124/index.html.",
  "source": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn_web_development/Extensions/Forms/Form_validation | https://www.w3.org/WAI/tutorials/forms/validation/ | https://www.frontendmentor.io/challenges/contact-form--G-hYlqKJj",
